-- French Stocks Advance; Danone, LVL Medical, Pernod-Ricard, Publicis Move
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2010-10-21T15:57:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/accor-itesoft-lvl-mersen-prodware-and-promeo-french-equity-preview.html
France’s CAC 40 Index climbed 50.12,
or 1.3 percent, to 3,878.27 at the 5:30 p.m. close of trading in
Paris. The SBF 120 Index also gained 1.3 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the French equity
market today.  Groupe Danone SA  (BN FP) gained 4.8 percent to 45.46 euros.
The company confirmed its targets for 2010 and said it plans a
500 million-euro ($699.7 million) share buyback with the
proceeds from the sale of stakes in businesses in Russia and
China.  LVL Medical Groupe  (LVL FP) rose 3 percent to 16.49 euros.
The French home healthcare company said its share buyback was
successful and that it bought back 6 percent of its shares for
20 euros each. Separately, the company said full-year revenue
rose to 155.7 million euros, from 136.1 million euros a year
earlier.  Mersen  (MRN FP) increased 4.1 percent to 32.57 euros. The
world’s biggest maker of brushes for electrical motors said
third-quarter sales rose 34 percent to 183 million euros, helped
by exchange rates and the acquisitions of Lumpp and Mingrong.  Pernod-Ricard SA  (RI FP) advanced 6.3 percent to 65.45
euros. The maker of Chivas Regal whiskey and Absolut vodka said
first-quarter “organic” sales, which exclude the effect of
acquisitions, disposals or currency swings, soared 10 percent,
beating a 4.5 percent median growth estimate of 8 analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg News.  Prodware  (ALPRO FP) soared 4.8 percent to 6.38 euros. The
computer-services company said nine-month revenue was 56.5
million euros compared with 56.2 million euros in the year-
earlier period.  Publicis Groupe SA  (PUB FP) advanced 4.6 percent to 37.39
euros. The owner of the Saatchi & Saatchi and Leo Burnett ad
agencies said third-quarter revenue rose 9.2 percent, led by
digital activities in North America and business in emerging
markets such as China.  To contact the reporter on this story:
